{"type": "article", "id": 57571, "title": "“一物多用”，是这套3D打印家居用品的最大特点｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2018-10-22T23:07:10Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 768, "name": "产品设计"}, {"id": 156, "name": "3D打印"}, {"id": 53654, "name": "Tivoli by Normann Copenhagen"}, {"id": 53655, "name": "SOL Motors"}, {"id": 32873, "name": "OTHR"}, {"id": 53656, "name": "SML"}, {"id": 53657, "name": "Vonnegut Kraft"}, {"id": 17376, "name": "Joe Doucet"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 12, "praise_count": 74, "image": "img/article/article_show/20181022234637Eqd6lA51PgwMU3eY.jpg", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px Helvetica; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font: 11.0px Helvetica; font-kerning: none} span.s3 {font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; font-kerning: none} span.s4 {text-decoration: underline ; font-kerning: none} span.s5 {font: 11.0px Helvetica; font-kerning: none; color: #0f1419; -webkit-text-stroke: 0px #0f1419} span.s6 {font-kerning: none; color: #0f1419; -webkit-text-stroke: 0px #0f1419} span.s7 {font-kerning: none; color: #657ab7; -webkit-text-stroke: 0px #657ab7} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Sonia Table Series by Vonnegut Kraft</h3><p>纽约设计工作室 Vonnegut Kraft 推出新品 Sonia 系列桌子，灵感来源于一种纺织品的印花图案，这种印花由女性艺术家 Sonia Delauney 在 1930 年设计，Metz &amp; Co 制造生产。桌子选材为木材和铝制品的组合，桌面造型模仿简单的网状印花设计：木材中间遍布重复的孔洞，像是布料肌理放大的效果，桌子边缘也模仿了布料的磨损边缘质感。</p><p>在网格之间的孔洞处，设计师略微打破网格和“磨损”边缘的平衡性，将支撑用的铝块穿过网格之间。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234711fESJp7mvDb6awhrN.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201810222347114hdBW8n5gZ3Hujqe.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234711K27EvuHfy6WAUGxS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234713v1wMLWHuSdQGJ7bF.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234713Z8yk6IGXinlrYKPB.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234742g64KQJzY7AfW8iLT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://vonnegutkraft.com/collection/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Vonnegut Kraft</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Flowing by SML</h3><p>最近，首尔建筑设计工作室 SML 推出全新家具系列 Flowing，包括一款座椅和一款桌子。粉色与黑色搭配的家具展示出手工绘制的涂鸦形态，而曲线的转角设计的灵感，据称来源于瀑布水流的形态。</p><p>Flowing 的支撑腿由连续的钢铁线条组成，其中外侧漆成黑色，内侧漆成粉色，这样的设计让家具看上去仿佛是画在纸面上一般。除了家具图形设计的简约特征之外，根据观赏角度不同，家具还能展现出多种不同的优雅建筑形态，例如支撑结构的拱形结构以及桌面与座椅靠背处的几何形态，似是又为妙趣十足的家具添入了更有意味的解读方式。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234846ehuJav5b2jC4SFQx.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.689487\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201810222348177EmgyVH2Y5iChbR0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234817m9kCjhHopuEng51Z.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.689487\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234817zFPeu3iE7rIaHhQ6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234817aWGPV7m3jO0ri1HE.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://www.sml.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">SML</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>3D-printed Vessels by Joe Doucet</h3><p>纽约工业设计师 Joe Doucet 去年推出了一个专做 3D 打印家居的品牌<a href=\"https://www.othr.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"> </a>OTHR，想要让设计师们利用这个技术掌握更多生产控制权。最近，Joe 为 Cooper Hewitt 博物馆的展览 Tablescapes：Designs for Dining 量身创作了一系列 3D 打印家居用品，包括餐具、炊具和收纳物件等等，意在体现“21 世纪的餐饮精神”，在设计时充分考量到资源有限的现况。</p><p>设计师秉持着“一物多用”的目的，赋予单一产品多种功能。例如，盖子可以用作盘子和三脚架，同时密封碗以保持盛装食物的新鲜度。凸起的圆点设计，不仅易于抓握，还能帮助用户在烹饪时均匀散热。</p><p>值得一提的是，这个系列的品类还凸显出跨文化传播的特质，中餐中常用的筷子与典型的西餐饮食餐具皆有。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234928RbqgajJNL0rCEAMT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.714467\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234928rLmgZpDEOklNe0VW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234928QlzL8SeZ9vV4hxr0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018102223492781yZWdk2b5zUKBvX.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562793\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022234929bthKGne6HBg8qmXQ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201810222350214ac690D1kbLJhO2P.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"https://www.dezeen.com/2018/10/18/joe-doucet-3d-printed-vessels-tablescapes-exhibition-cooper-hewitt/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Dezeen</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>SOL Motors Pocket Rocket</h3><p>在早先科隆举行的 INTERMOT 国际电车展上，德国品牌 SOL Motors 展示了一款全新设计的迷你电动单车 Pocket Rocket。以 Pocket 命名，可想而知它的体积并非一般电单车，体量更加迷你，但却有更强的动力。</p><p>它的设计很简单，基本上车身设计就是由一条水管形的圆筒，配合简单的线条组成，简约又很抓人眼球。座位高度仅有 82 厘米，以轻量铝金属结构制作的 Pocket Rocket，重量只有 55 千克。</p><p>Pocket Rocket 配备了一个 8.5 匹马力的电动马达，官方宣称每次充电后可行驶 80km，最高时速也可达 80km，刹车备有动力回收系统以延长续航力。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235047tGRNJ1efTZgX47Eu.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.654687\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235047VfjU8mu2Xsy1poaO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235048oQq09ZClaK6TrSe5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235048UmubrGi5aDlV324y.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235048e8LVMTShNoE5Qply.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235048Hhbyj6RLkYGdlmgv.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235047eg4OCSlGKZDTHcd6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://sol-motors.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">SOL Motors</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Trumpet Lamp by Tivoli by Normann Copenhagen</h3><p>丹麦设计品牌 Normann Copenhagen 与哥本哈根 Tivoli 乐园合作的新系列中，有一款名为“号角”的吊灯，造型源于 Tivoli 乐园中少年音乐团所用的乐器，乐团成立于 1844 年，演奏至今。</p><p>“号角”吊灯将丹麦照明设计的丰富历史与 Tivoli 乐园中的层叠设计融合起来，超大尺寸的双层钢制喇叭口造型，创造出了独特且舒适的定向光源。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235155kIqCM9ZpVHGc2FYb.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.625106\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201810222351563cRZh1lk8f0dzoHW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.215200\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20181022235123LRT2vZyrhKEQantO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.625106\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：Tivoli by Normann Copenhagen</figcaption></figure></div>"}